## HENDRIKOV Гендриков 1010061


## GRABBE Граббе 1010062
# Граббе, Павел Христофорович ( December 2, 1789 , Kexholm , Grand Duchy of Finland - July 15, 1875 , Timchikha estate , Poltava province ) 
		# 1m: 1825 - Vera Mikhailovna Skoropadskaya (1801-1828), daughter of Colonel Mikhail Yakovlevich Skoropadsky (1764-1810); niece of A. S. Khvostov 's wife . Died three years after marriage; she was buried with her 2-month-old son Nikolai in the Spaso-Andronikov Monastery.
		# 2m: 1830 Ekaterina Evstafyevna Rolle (d. 1851), the daughter of a Bessarabian doctor of medicine, whom Grabbe met in Iasi. According to contemporaries, she was short, black-haired, swarthy, with features found on antique Greek cameos. She was weird and cheated on her husband. On August 21, 1851, she committed suicide by shooting herself with a pistol. Children:
	# Sophia , wife of Ivan Petrovich Mosolov
	# Olga , died at a young age
	# Alexander (1838-1863), staff captain, participant in the Caucasian War and the suppression of the uprising of 1863-1864 , died of wounds received in the battle of Sendzejowice .
	# Catherine (1839-27.03.1888), wife of Baron Alexander Pavel von Vietinghoff (1836-1896), died of pneumonia [5] .
	# Vladimir (1843-1893), major general
	100084286={ #// Ct Nikolai Grabbe (1832-1896); m.Aleksandra Orlova-Denissova (24 Feb 1837-6 Mar 1892) $$

		1896.01.01={death=yes}
	}

				# m.(04/28/1891) - Sofya Ivanovna Vsevolozhskaya (1869-1952), maid of honor, daughter of Chief Chamberlain I. V. Vsevolozhsky . Since 1936, she was the chairman of the Don Women's Committee, and since March 1939 - the Charitable Association of Don Ladies in France. Buried in Paris. Their kids:
			# Elizabeth (1892-1962), maid of honor (01/01/1912), in her first marriage (since January 27, 1912) [2] married to Baron Vladimir Anatolyevich Palen, in the second - von Muffling.
